Package edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.course

Class Activity

java.lang.Object
edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.course.Activity
All Implemented Interfaces:
Conflict
Direct Known Subclasses:
Course
public abstract class Activity extends Object implements Conflict
Activity class contains the course title, meeting days, start time, and end time so that it can help the schedule to hold both Courses and Events classes. This is the superclass of the Course and Event classes that holds the general and similar information so that its subclasses can expand more on their differences.
Author:
Hari Vemulapalli

    • setMeetingDaysAndTime

      public void setMeetingDaysAndTime(String meetingDays, int startTime, int endTime)
      Sets the Activity's meeting days, start time, and end time. If meeting days are characters other than 'M', 'T', 'W', 'H', 'F', or 'A', If there are duplicates of these characters, If start time and/or end time is not between 0000 and 2359, If end time is less than start time, and if a start time and/or end time is listed when meeting days is "A", an IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.
      Parameters:
      meetingDays - - days when the activity will meet
      startTime - - time when the activity starts
      endTime - - time when the activity ends
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - when the parameters meetingDays, startTime, and/or endTime is invalid
